cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

The paper proposes an unsupervised feature learning algorithm that achieves state-of-the-art performance on the STL-10 dataset. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The algorithm also exploits a new way of optimizing for sparsity, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's performance on image classification, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
